          <num>245-58</num>
          <heading>Section 245-58</heading>
          <content>
            <p>[§245-58]  Illegal sale of export or foreign
cigarettes; revocation or suspension of license; civil penalties.
If any
licensee violates this part or any rule adopted pursuant to this part, the
director may:
(1)  Revoke or suspend the licensee's license pursuant
to procedures complying with chapter 91; and
(2)  Impose a civil penalty in an amount not to exceed
the greater of five times the retail value of the cigarettes involved, or
$5,000. [L 2000, c 201, pt of §1]
